Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.47,0:00:08.31,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Abandoned artificial satellites.\NTanks jettisoned from shuttles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.31,0:00:11.28,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Refuse generated during\nspace station construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.28,0:00:18.44,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,This vast amount of junk floating in space,\nspace debris, is a very serious threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.12,0:00:25.96,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,This is a story of 2075, a time in which\nthis space garbage has become a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.48,0:02:02.93,F.O. (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(506,430,305,438)}{\bord0.1\fs17\fscx95\fscy95}{\t(0,6110,(\fscx165\fscy165)}{\fad(300,800)}Return Trajectory
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.39,0:02:12.13,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, what should I write here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.13,0:02:13.83,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What are you\nasking me for?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.27,0:02:18.29,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody says that you've sent in more written\napologies than anyone else, so I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.44,0:02:20.77,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,They did, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.84,0:02:22.94,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.94,0:02:25.51,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, fine.\NWrite down what I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.51,0:02:26.31,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.55,0:02:29.31,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"Sorry about nearly screwing up\nyour flight."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.31,0:02:32.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"But we might end up doing it again,\nso bear with us, okay?"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.19,0:02:36.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, you'll never be popular\nwith the girls with that attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.82,0:02:40.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody asked you. The girls with\nan eye for quality are lookin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.63,0:02:42.19,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,They go, "I've had my eye\non you for ages!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.19,0:02:46.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"I've worried myself sick with you\nworking such a dangerous job!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.60,0:02:49.13,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I{\fs24}t{\fs26} was like this during the\N"my spaceship" incident, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.47,0:02:53.04,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Why are all of your fantasies like\nsomething out of a comic book?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:55.88,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Look here, rookie! How about showing\nyour senpai a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.01,0:02:57.24,Alternative (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hello there, Hoshino Hachirota-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.38,0:03:01.12,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Um... And you are...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.13,0:03:03.62,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I've had my eye on you\nfor ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.55,0:03:08.78,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I worry myself sick with you\Nworking such a dangerous job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.09,0:03:13.21,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,There are so many things I want\nyou to tell me about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.21,0:03:15.63,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure, if there's anything\NI can do to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.73,0:03:17.77,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Then, would you mind\nsigning this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.60,0:03:21.37,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't let your guard down\njust because you're young!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.37,0:03:23.34,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Outer space\nis full of dangers!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.34,0:03:26.24,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Cosmic Life Insurance is there\nfor life's little surprises. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.24,0:03:27.26,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Insurance?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.31,0:03:29.24,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,GET OUT!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.24,0:03:31.90,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I love how you play\nhard to get!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.91,0:03:37.95,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, there's insurance solicitation\neven in space...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.95,0:03:39.95,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Especially at this time\nof year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.95,0:03:40.78,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,This time of year?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.52,0:03:45.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Accidents are covered, naturally, as are\nall of your family's medical expenses!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:47.46,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I already have insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.46,0:03:49.43,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true\nat all, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.43,0:03:53.29,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,My company's insurance is unlike\nany insurance that's come before!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.60,0:03:56.13,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,They say that, but it's the same old thing every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.60,0:03:54.88,Alternative (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Can I have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.86,0:03:56.13,Alternative (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Have them all if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:03:57.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi, this one's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:03:57.13,Alternative (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0062,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.84,0:04:00.07,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Man, what a pain\nin the ass...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.07,0:04:02.39,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Just use the one I turned in\nlast year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.39,0:04:05.51,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Company policy is that you\nmake a new one every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:07.06,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,And one for you, Tanabe-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.91,0:04:09.52,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What's this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.85,0:04:11.15,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Your last will\nand testament.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.05,0:04:15.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Once you've written it, put it in\nthe envelope, seal it, and turn it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:17.38,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,The deadline is the end\nof the week, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.49,0:04:20.78,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Last will\nand testament?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.26,0:04:24.74,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, you mean that thing\nyou write for when you die?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.90,0:04:25.64,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.64,0:04:28.40,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,In this job, there's no telling\nwhen you might die.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.40,0:04:30.92,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you almost died\na while back, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.57,0:04:32.10,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.10,0:04:34.97,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Life insurance is for those\N"You're kidding" times in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.97,0:04:37.04,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Preparedness is peace of mind.\NSatisfaction once you're signed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.04,0:04:38.59,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,And it lowers\nyour tax bill, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.59,0:04:41.43,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Um, what should I do\nabout insurance?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.43,0:04:43.05,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I{\fs24}t{\fs26}'s your call.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.05,0:04:47.39,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"Will Season" is when they\nmake their money,\Nso I'm sure they'll be happy\nto tell you all about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.39,0:04:51.39,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It's also a good opportunity to give some thought\Nto what'll happen after you die\nand stuff like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.46,0:04:54.23,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You give insurance salesmen\na bad name!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.43,0:04:57.99,Other (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,All insurance company personnel,\nplease make sure to register with reception.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.60,0:05:05.12,Other (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Permits are valid for all one-G and zero-G blocks,\Nso long as they are under Technora jurisdiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.12,0:05:07.44,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,A small premium will give you\nlifelong coverage!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.44,0:05:09.01,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It'll give you peace of mind\nin your golden years!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.01,0:05:11.04,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You'll recoup your investment\nonce it reaches maturity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.04,0:05:14.75,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...so you get the best deal by signing up\nfor these things while you're still young!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.75,0:05:16.51,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and how about you,\nyoung man?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.51,0:05:18.34,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,No thanks.\NI'm with Vega Corp, so l...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.34,0:05:21.30,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! I'll see you\nnext month, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.52,0:05:23.51,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Please, for heaven's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.51,0:05:26.39,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,My company is rated triple-A,\nso choose mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.63,0:05:32.73,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Three months! Just for three months!\NI'll give you all the little gifts I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.50,0:05:36.23,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if it's just three\nmonths, maybe I could...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.23,0:05:37.20,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:38.53,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,C-Can't breathe...!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:39.20,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.20,0:05:39.97,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.97,0:05:42.61,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,But I have a quota to meet!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.27,0:05:42.61,Alternative (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.31,0:05:47.33,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,The most annoying season of the year\nis upon us once again, isn't it, Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.33,0:05:51.22,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,When you listen to those agents give their spiel,\nyou end up signing something somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.22,0:05:54.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,We're in Debris Section,\nbut we mostly do desk work...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.42,0:06:00.09,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about ready to retire, so I don't need\ninsurance that costs that much...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.09,0:06:02.46,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I have got a great idea, Chief!\NI call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.79,0:06:06.23,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,..."Operation See no Evil,\NSpeak no Evil, Hear no Evil."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.56,0:06:08.64,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,If we do that, they can't\nsell us anything, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.64,0:06:10.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's\na good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:13.48,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it, though? I was up all\nlast night coming up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.81,0:06:15.27,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Lavie! Look down!\NLook down!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.87,0:06:16.88,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.88,0:06:18.98,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about that,\njust put that back!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:19.44,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.78,0:06:25.82,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear Mom and Dad, please forgive the sadness\NI've caused by dying before you."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.02,0:06:30.96,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"Dear Dad. Rock music doesn't\nwork with funerals, so don't..."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.96,0:06:32.18,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's no good...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.76,0:06:35.98,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"Write out your last will,"\nthey say...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:42.03,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.37,0:06:44.06,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.34,0:06:48.34,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Who said you could\nlook at that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.34,0:06:51.28,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I was just, uh...\NWhat is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.28,0:06:52.33,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,My last will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.06,0:06:57.48,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You were told to write one, too, remember?\NThey said to turn it in by the end of the week.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.75,0:06:59.98,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Your last will? Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.25,0:07:02.61,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What, you got a problem with that\nor something?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.61,0:07:07.03,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,But a will is supposed to have things like parting\nwords for parents or friends, or thanks for...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.03,0:07:08.29,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have anything\nto say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:09.49,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.49,0:07:11.83,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying goodbye!\NYou're dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.83,0:07:15.79,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I{\fs24}t{\fs26} doesn't matter what I write.\NOnce I'm dead, it's all over for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.97,0:07:18.20,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That's the coldest thing I've ever heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:21.25,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,If they saw a will like this, the people you\nleave behind would break down in tears!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.25,0:07:24.17,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You think so? I kinda think\nthey'd bust out laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.38,0:07:26.17,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,This is no good!\NRewrite it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.42,0:07:30.64,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable... What did I ever do to deserve\nbeing lectured by the likes of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.66,0:07:39.23,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Here.\NHappy now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.19,0:07:43.52,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.83,0:07:50.06,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,All this stuff about last wills just isn't\nhitting home for me, to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:53.70,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I{\fs24}t{\fs26}'s not like we go out\ninto space all that often.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.70,0:07:57.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,But my section does go out,\nso it makes me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.88,0:08:00.64,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What are the other Debris Section\npeople writing in theirs?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.88,0:08:02.88,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Like that diaper guy,\nfor instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.15,0:08:05.09,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Sketch Boy,\nyou mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.32,0:08:06.38,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Sketch Boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:09.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,The jerk drew a sketch\nas his last will!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.42,0:08:12.93,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you normally write down heartfelt words\nfor the people who were important to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.73,0:08:17.00,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Well, in the end, a last will\nis a personal thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.00,0:08:18.69,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I still don't think\nit's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.06,0:08:20.40,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I{\fs24}t{\fs26} must be love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.43,0:08:24.00,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That person is on\nyour mind a lot, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.00,0:08:27.94,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Lucie, why are you trying\nto turn this into a love affair?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.94,0:08:31.31,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Because I don't believe that\nmen and women can be "just friends."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.31,0:08:33.44,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,And what about all those\ninsurance salesmen, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.68,0:08:37.18,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right! I got suckered\ninto a married couple's plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.18,0:08:37.92,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting married?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.93,0:08:38.68,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.68,0:08:39.75,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I don't date coworkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.75,0:08:41.02,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno, I might.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.02,0:08:42.05,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Who, that pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.05,0:08:43.65,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Cheng-Shin-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.09,0:08:47.83,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That's the last of our interior\nmaintenance work, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.83,0:08:52.63,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. Oh, and about my chief's parakeet...\NCould I leave him with you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.83,0:08:55.39,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You mean MacEnroe?\NSure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.87,0:08:57.23,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep pushing him\noff on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.57,0:08:58.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.60,0:08:59.54,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:09:03.06,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go ahead and send out a second\NFishbone. There's just too much debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.27,0:09:04.08,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.08,0:09:08.51,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. Miss Tanabe probably can't\nhandle one yet, so I'll take it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.51,0:09:09.75,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks,\nthat's a big help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.75,0:09:13.16,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,So, is our little Tanabe\nstill writing her last will?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:16.29,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, she seems to be\nagonizing over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.29,0:09:17.62,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I offer her\nsome advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.96,0:09:19.66,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,No, leave her be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.66,0:09:25.08,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What's important isn't\nwhat she writes, but that she learns that this\nis a job that might get her killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.54,0:09:34.61,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, about our last wills...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.61,0:09:37.01,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What, you're still racking your brain over that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.01,0:09:41.01,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Go with your gut with this stuff.\NYou gotta clear your head and start writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.01,0:09:42.68,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.98,0:09:46.72,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,When I start thinking about what I'll leave to my\nparents and friends, or what I should leave, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.05,0:09:48.41,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Leave behind, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.92,0:09:52.40,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What they want you to leave\nthem is money. Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.40,0:09:53.79,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.79,0:09:54.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Not again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.84,0:09:57.03,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,So, have you thought\nit over?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:09:58.05,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.26,0:10:03.46,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Like she said just now, deciding what to leave\nyour loved ones is a difficult question, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.46,0:10:09.92,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs22}But with money they can convert it into all sorts of things, such as goods, but also\nmedical treatment or an education.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.92,0:10:11.71,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.71,0:10:14.68,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What will make a person happy\nvaries from person to person, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.18,0:10:18.51,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,So don't you think the best thing is to leave it\nup to the person who's going to use it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:19.52,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.52,0:10:20.89,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That's not right at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.89,0:10:22.35,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.35,0:10:26.35,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs25}Personally, I think\nit's better than giving someone something they don't want and having it go to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.35,0:10:28.81,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a question of\ngaining or losing things!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.30,0:10:33.03,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying that leaving money behind\nwhen you die is too sad for words!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.03,0:10:36.99,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you think so? What do you plan\non leaving to your loved ones, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.24,0:10:39.95,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave them love!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.21,0:10:41.97,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Love...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.97,0:10:45.27,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! That's it!\NI should leave behind love!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.61,0:10:47.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Love is insurance\nenough, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.55,0:10:50.95,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I see.\NWell, to each his own, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.25,0:10:54.13,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you again, Hachirota-san.\NThink it over, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.32,0:10:56.02,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe if I get\na bonus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.02,0:10:58.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That's it... Love was the\nanswer all along...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.96,0:11:01.33,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Y'know, in a sense,\nyou're amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.33,0:11:01.87,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.93,0:11:03.49,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Or at least unpretentious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.49,0:11:05.33,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I was impressed, I have to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.26,0:11:09.17,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,She'll leave love, huh?\NThat girl is a real find.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.17,0:11:12.17,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're only laughing 'cause you\ndon't have to work with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.17,0:11:14.41,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That girl is\nseriously scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.41,0:11:18.81,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I think she's right, though. You should put some\nthought into it when you're writing your will.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.81,0:11:21.35,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but I sorta think\nthey're both wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.25,0:11:26.91,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Money or words or whatever,\nthat's not what I want to leave when I'm gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.12,0:11:32.29,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,But when somebody asks me what I'm gonna\nleave behind, I don't have an answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:36.76,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Rest assured, sir! We're rated\nnumber one in the industry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.76,0:11:40.72,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm begging you! If I don't meet\nmy quota this month, they'll... Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.20,0:11:42.10,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.10,0:11:45.07,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there... Hang in there... I just need\nto make it through this one last season.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.80,0:11:49.94,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Remember, Chief, I was the one\nwho came up with this nice little plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.31,0:11:53.18,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Chief, this paperwork\nis all right, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.18,0:11:56.05,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,This way, I won't sign up for\ninsurance that I don't need!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.05,0:11:56.68,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.68,0:12:00.64,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Recommend me as your replacement\nonce you retire, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.12,0:12:03.31,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You can check this, too, Manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.29,0:12:07.37,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Do some work,\ndamn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.06,0:12:12.20,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, about that will...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.20,0:12:14.34,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Crap, you're persistent!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.34,0:12:15.92,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I mean yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.30,0:12:21.07,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking, and, well,\ndoes a last will have to be words?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.64,0:12:24.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think I drew a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.60,0:12:27.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,No, what about a movie letter\nor something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.05,0:12:30.58,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,With words, you sound formal,\nbut with a movie letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.58,0:12:33.32,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...you could be lighthearted about it,\nlike you were calling your mom or dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.32,0:12:36.32,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that!\NI can't call my old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.56,0:12:39.72,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, I didn't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.89,0:12:42.43,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, he's alive.\NAlive, kicking, and then some.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.43,0:12:46.24,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Did you have a falling out? Shouldn't you have\noutgrown your rebellious phase by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.56,0:12:47.63,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't make\nyour father worry...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.63,0:12:48.39,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.33,0:12:52.32,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,A stupid coworker doesn't have any right\nto butt into my family life!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.90,0:12:55.30,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting on my damn nerves\nwith all your nagging!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.97,0:12:59.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yuri, I'm glad we had you\ncome out here to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.38,0:13:02.55,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,There's too much to handle\nwith just me and the rookie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.05,0:13:06.51,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Guys, could I talk you\ninto some overtime?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.92,0:13:10.15,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the short notice, but there's a piece\nof debris that I want you to pick up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.39,0:13:15.50,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like something that was on a short-period cometary orbit got grabbed by Earth's gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.52,0:13:17.99,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it's just scrap metal\nor something, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.23,0:13:20.74,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,We've already got a pretty\nbig haul as it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.74,0:13:25.16,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,They say there's a research agency that wants it.\NPlus, you're already in the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.07,0:13:28.50,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Save the complaints.\NIt's for research, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.21,0:13:32.23,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.28,0:13:40.46,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Preparedness is peace of mind!\NSatisfaction once you're signed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.46,0:13:42.13,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Accidents are covered, of course,\nas are you're family's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:43.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Three months, that's all I ask!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.61,0:13:45.09,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,We're rated number one in the industry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.09,0:13:47.64,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Our company offers\N300% peace of mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.64,0:13:50.35,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Please, just look it over...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.17,0:13:57.36,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hello there, Miss! Have you settled\non an insurance company yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.80,0:13:59.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm a temp worker.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.84,0:14:03.93,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so? Well, I'll leave a\npamphlet on the desk just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.34,0:14:05.71,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need any, you jerk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.21,0:14:12.01,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Chief, but I'm\nabandoning ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.92,0:14:16.98,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,How about it? Shouldn't you\nthink of your children's future?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.26,0:14:20.36,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Our tuition plan was put together\nwith exactly that in mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.36,0:14:21.46,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bargain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.36,0:14:24.11,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,How many of you people\nare there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.97,0:14:34.37,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.84,0:14:36.15,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What is that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.34,0:14:37.18,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.25,0:14:43.77,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I-lt's a...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.23,0:14:47.08,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Holy crap, would you look\nat that expression?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.72,0:14:49.15,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He's smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.15,0:14:50.69,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Is that seriously a...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.69,0:14:52.91,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,A coffin from\na space burial.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.39,0:14:57.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It's written right here.\N"Astronaut lbn Fadlan."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.42,0:15:02.12,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"In accordance with his final wishes,\nhe set sail into the infinite sea. 2024."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.27,0:15:04.70,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That was right before space\nburials were banned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.70,0:15:07.24,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It's a corpse from\nmore than 50 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.24,0:15:10.07,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been launched on a heading\nto leave the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.41,0:15:11.85,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...but it looks like\nhe came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:16.00,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He must've wanted to reach\nthe edge of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:18.98,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...but he couldn't\nbreak free of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.40,0:15:25.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,The odds against this are incredible.\NIt's damn near a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.76,0:15:29.82,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,On that orbit, his next rendezvous with Earth\nwouldn't have been for another 700 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.82,0:15:31.83,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What's going to be done\nwith the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.83,0:15:34.04,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know, don't care.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.04,0:15:37.25,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Our job's to collect debris,\nend of story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.25,0:15:39.58,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, debris?\NThat's a person's body!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.17,0:15:43.71,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Any useless object floating around\nin space is debris, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.71,0:15:45.57,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be\nso coldhearted?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.84,0:15:47.67,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It's proof that he\nwas alive once!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.30,0:15:50.88,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're unbelievable,\ntreating that man like a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.88,0:15:54.22,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,How many times am I gonna have to spell out\nyour job description before it sinks in?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.32,0:15:55.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Good work, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.69,0:15:59.16,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Fee-san, what's gonna happen\nto that body?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.39,0:16:02.02,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Control Section is contacting\nhis next of kin as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.33,0:16:05.44,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,They said that legally speaking, the body\nis the property of the next of kin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.44,0:16:08.93,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,This is Seven Delivery.\NYou are cleared for flight to Baikonur...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.93,0:16:10.70,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're certain that\nit's my father?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.94,0:16:13.67,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am. This is\na most unusual case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.94,0:16:17.32,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,As far as burials conducted\nprior to 2028 are concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.68,0:16:20.04,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...you would be able to re-bury him\nas a special exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:21.04,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.48,0:16:22.24,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.68,0:16:24.96,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be possible for me to speak\nwith the people who recovered him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.82,0:16:29.06,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Astronaut Fadlan's daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.35,0:16:33.72,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She says she'd like to speak with you face\nto face, so I'm going to patch her through.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.23,0:16:35.06,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.06,0:16:36.32,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.40,0:16:42.56,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Fee Carmichael, captain of the DS-12, the\nship that recovered Astronaut Fadlan's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.56,0:16:48.53,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Um... This is an awkward question,\nbut how did my father's body look?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.77,0:16:53.97,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm ashamed to say it, but I\nnever looked at my father's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.99,0:16:59.00,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He was smiling.\NHe must've had a full life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.09,0:17:02.46,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.69,0:17:04.90,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Is something\nthe matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.46,0:17:10.36,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Father... My father was an astronaut\nthrough and through.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.88,0:17:14.90,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He was extremely proud of his work\nas the pilot of a spaceplane,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.13,0:17:19.03,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...and he seldom returned to the home\nwhere we were waiting for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.27,0:17:22.97,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,But he grew sick\nfrom cosmic radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.97,0:17:26.07,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...and soon after he retired,\nhe passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.54,0:17:29.54,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He stated in his will that he\ndidn't want to be buried on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.01,0:17:33.75,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I was afraid\nto look at my father's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.19,0:17:37.79,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that once we held the space burial,\NI would never be able to see him again,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.79,0:17:40.76,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...but when I wondered to myself what sort\nof expression he had on his face, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.76,0:17:47.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, my mother and I were not\nmentioned at all in his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.12,0:17:50.53,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He was a man whose eyes\nwere always on the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.53,0:17:54.88,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...and even when he did look at me, they were\nalways focused on a point far beyond me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.59,0:18:00.10,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Father's eyes were always\nlocked on deep space.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.25,0:18:05.91,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true...?\NSo, Father was smiling, was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.69,0:18:11.93,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Father... Please send Father\nback into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:16.41,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. In that case,\nwe'll see to re-burying him ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.73,0:18:18.43,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for all\nyour trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.26,0:18:21.50,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I think this is what my father\nwould have wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.67,0:18:24.11,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,No, you can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.48,0:18:25.57,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.57,0:18:27.17,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Tanabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.17,0:18:29.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You can't send your father\nback into space!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.07,0:18:31.96,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're his family,\nso he should be with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.21,0:18:36.70,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, rookie, you haven't been in space that long,\nso don't start talking like you own the place!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.48,0:18:39.12,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Your father's precious to you,\nisn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.12,0:18:41.85,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Whether he's in Earth or space,\nthat doesn't change!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.99,0:18:43.75,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.75,0:18:45.42,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, just let\nthat little twerp go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.42,0:18:48.31,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What she says does make\nsome sense, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.49,0:18:54.71,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable... What is it with astronauts\nand trying to act tough?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.72,0:18:57.33,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then. Our company\nwill ship him to the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.33,0:18:59.89,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,...where we'll fire him towards extra-solar space\nusing the mass driver there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.37,0:19:01.20,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.47,0:19:03.67,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.67,0:19:04.80,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.04,0:19:08.38,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi, we're heading for the graveyard orbit.\NPass word to Tanabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.38,0:19:11.70,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. Hey, rookie! How long\nare you gonna keep sulking?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.85,0:19:15.59,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.59,0:19:17.13,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That little idiot opened\nthe cargo container!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.99,0:19:24.30,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell\nis that rookie thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.30,0:19:27.52,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna have to wring her neck\nto let her know who's boss around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:31.88,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe, come back! Tanabe!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.88,0:19:33.76,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, girl,\nanswer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.17,0:19:36.74,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Get your ass back\nin here, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.01,0:19:41.61,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.75,0:19:44.58,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying\nto pull, rookie?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:46.25,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come near me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.48,0:19:49.60,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,If you come any closer, I'll chuck\nthis thing into the atmosphere!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.26,0:19:52.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.16,0:19:54.59,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.76,0:19:56.12,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.46,0:19:58.83,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're an idiot.\NA bottomless pit of stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.10,0:20:01.30,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What good is that\ngonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.30,0:20:05.02,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that will you wrote!\NYou're the one with the problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:09.51,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you understand?!\NWe can't send this man back into space!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.51,0:20:11.91,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That's not up to you\nto decide!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.94,0:20:14.67,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That man wanted\nto be buried in space!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.91,0:20:17.72,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,As a fellow astronaut,\NI understand how he feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.72,0:20:18.92,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Let's give him\nwhat he wants!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.92,0:20:22.19,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong! Mr. Fadlan\nregretted his decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.19,0:20:25.41,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He was drifting in space and he\nsaid to himself, "I want to go back!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.41,0:20:27.56,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,How can you say that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.56,0:20:30.50,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ignore the man's wishes\nand force your own dreams on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:35.33,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,But Mr. Fadlan came back!\NAgainst astronomical odds!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.47,0:20:36.84,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You yourself said\nit was a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.84,0:20:38.77,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,A miracle?\NWhat are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.09,0:20:41.36,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,And why do you suppose\nthat miracle happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:44.04,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Because Mr. Fadlan\nwished for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.24,0:20:46.56,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted it so bad that\nit made a miracle happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.97,0:20:50.48,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "I want to go back to Earth!\NI want to go back to my family!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.48,0:20:52.35,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong!\NIt was just a coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.35,0:20:53.37,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It was a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.85,0:20:56.89,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you go saying what\nyou want to hear, Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.89,0:21:01.40,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this?! It was his\nown choice to live alone and die alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.63,0:21:03.46,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,And it was\nthe wrong decision!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.46,0:21:06.62,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, Fadlan-sama is loved by people, isn't he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.62,0:21:10.76,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,By his wife, his daughter, and I bet\neven his parents and friends, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.79,0:21:15.93,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,A man like that can't be selfish and decide to\nturn into a mummy at the ends of the universe!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.41,0:21:20.78,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,He should go back to Earth!\NIsn't that what love's all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.18,0:21:25.21,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, I'd want to go back and be\nwith my loved ones, even if I was dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.08,0:21:29.38,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Living alone\nand dying alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.62,0:21:30.65,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.56,0:21:33.79,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,How could anyone\nbe satisfied with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.12,0:21:35.19,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It's stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.93,0:21:42.33,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Space is too big\nto face all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.64,0:21:47.54,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.54,0:21:55.66,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Put the coffin down, Tanabe. His daughter\nsays she wants to claim the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.49,0:22:04.27,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.72,0:22:07.69,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,But I've already sent the forms\nover to Welfare Section...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.56,0:22:10.26,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.26,0:22:11.43,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.86,0:22:15.35,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot of hoops to jump through\nto send a body back to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.63,0:22:19.50,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Still, after all those things she said,\nshe has to be the one to deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.52,0:22:22.71,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,The written report?\NI'm submitting it to INTO, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.21,0:22:24.67,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It's not written properly?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.01,0:22:28.27,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on...\NIt was around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.12,0:22:34.39,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much\nfor the contracts!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.39,0:22:35.92,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me, Mother...!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.92,0:22:37.39,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,What do I need with\na student loan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.16,0:22:42.64,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.43,0:22:45.76,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Looks like you\ngot your contracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.03,0:22:48.57,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I still haven't got one from you, though.\NHow about this, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.57,0:22:51.90,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,It's our top of the line item.\NThe "Double Plan for Lovers."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.57,0:22:53.87,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,"Love," my ass...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.94,0:22:56.04,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I don't buy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.74,0:22:59.30,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,No way in hell is the universe\nthat sentimental!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.91,0:24:58.68,F.O. (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,{\shad0.5\bord0.2\fscx105\1c&HD2BEAC&\move(220,20,395,20)\fad(0,250)}Next Time:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.91,0:24:58.68,F.O. (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\shad0.5\bord0.2\fscx105\1c&HD2BEAC&\move(435,372,240,372)\fad(0,500)}Part of the Job
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.40,0:24:37.13,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Could you please stop\nwith that "rookie" stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.13,0:24:40.11,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Colin Clifford.\NMaybe you've heard of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.25,0:24:45.12,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Why does it have to be us?\NGo make the PR Section do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.45,0:24:47.82,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,We're doing this\nto help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.84,0:24:51.47,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,That way, your parents would never know\nthat you collect garbage in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.47,0:24:55.46,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,You do the same pathetic job,\nday in and day out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.76,0:24:58.06,Standard (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,Debris collectors are\nas cool as they come!
